				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">AE song/gear questions<a name="51466"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 12 04 3:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Greetings, first time bard poster here.
<br />

<br />
First off, awesome site.  I read alot of stuff here about AE kiting the cougars in Iceclad.  I've played EQ for about 3 years but never seriously played a bard, only toyed with it in PC and such.  Yesterday I took my lvl 27 bard to Iceclad to try to apply the AE kiting techniques I read about here.
<br />

<br />
I started with one, as recommended, and within a couple hours I was doing both islands at once.  Cougars only, if I could help it.
<br />

<br />
In 6 hours I went from one blue into 27 to level 32.  Holy smack.  All I can say is... go do this if you're a high 20s / low 30s bard.
<br />

<br />
I was using lvl 18 song DDD with a McVax horn equipped.  I screwed around with trying to twist in other songs (CoD and BBB).
<br />

<br />
Some questions:
<br />

<br />
1)     Is it just me, or does using just DDD work just as quickly or quicker than using DDD/CoD ?  Whenever I tried using both songs I noticed no appreciable gain.  Does one song step on the other?  I always believe in trying things for yourself to form your own opinions and get experience, but it seems I killed things more quickly using just DDD.
<br />

<br />
2)     Assuming I don't want to charm just yet, but rather DoT away at a hoarde I'm circling, what combination of songs have you found the most effective for killing the hoarde most quickly?
<br />

<br />
3)     What instrument(s) should I equip using your song recommendations in question (2)?
<br />

<br />
4)     Do Extended Range focus items work for songs?
<br />

<br />
5)     Is there a quick way to instrument swap, i.e. hotkeys?  Or do I have to open inventory and click swap ?
<br />

<br />
6)     How do I set up a hotkey to target a new mob in the hoarde without having to &quot;face&quot; the hoarde?  When I use my hotkey to target the nearest mob it doesn't work if they are not in my field of view - is there a way around this?
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance for your responses,
<br />

<br />
Mezart
<br />
35 Human Bard
<br />
Lanys T'Vyl
<br />
</span></td>
