				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE song/gear questions<a name="51540"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 12 04 8:26 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>#6 you can't without breaking EULA.
<br />

<br />
#5 EQInterface.com, you have to register but worth it.  There are HOTKEY banks customized that have your inventory and weapons slots always availible so that you can swap out fast.
<br />

<br />
#4 The only thing that extends our songs ranges is the AA Extended Notes and only works on beneficial songs.  It was broken at first and all songs benefited from it, but no longer.
<br />

<br />
#3 This is a case where you must swap out instruments, up to 3 of them, unless you have a set up like I tended to use prior to getting my epic... Tear Shaped Ring, Troubadour's Mace and Thunderous Drums of Karana.  At your level, it would probably be best to get and use sow potions and forget the drum for AE kiting; that means only 2 instruments and songs to twist.
<br />

<br />
#2 I am going to assume from the way you worded this that you mean AE kite, in that case both of your PBAoE damage type songs.
<br />

<br />
#1 you will drop mobs faster using both as they are DoT and last 3 full ticks each.  By stacking the 2 AE dots you are doing more damage.  The problem may be in your timing of your passing the mobs close when the song is going to land.  CoD has a range of 30 while DDD has a range of 35.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
