				<td colspan="2"><span>I believe, though it's possible they let it slip through, you cannot target something you cannot see.  If it is behind you, you can't see it.  I know that you can't use the Cycle Nearest NPC to target anything that you cannot see, including a mob right behind you pounding on your back.  I think, however, that if you go to 3rd person view you might be able to.
<br />

<br />
Still, to the best of my knowledge you cannot target something behind you with any hotkey/macro.  I'll test to be sure.</span></td>
